it’s got the blueberry aroma which is nice and a clean wheat taste, but when i see blueberry in the name and see it’s labeled as a fruit beer, i really wanna taste the blueberry. it’s a wheat beer with a scent of blueberry. it’s a decent wheat ale
nice light malty character in any kolsch. a little bit more bitter than im used to for a kolsch, but still is refreshing
really smooth and refreshing and juicy and light. i don’t have a pun for this one just like the beer
it’s a light sessionable ipa. aroma is nice but was hoping for a little more hop taste. i know it’s sessionable but could have a little more flavor
very crushable. not as aromatic and juicy tasting as other New England’s and more bitter, but it’s fairly balanced. i like it and would SLAM these
a gourmet corona. feliz cinco de mayo
an aromatic and juicy neipa. how MAGICAL
nice and bitter and piney and aromatic but still kind of light. this is good. no pun today have a good night
this is a sipper but has a nice clove taste
heavily hoppy but not bitter. if y’all know the griffin ride at Busch Gardens, it’s just like the first drop on the ride: unexpected yet strong
really refreshing af. can have this for the last minute and first minute anytime it’s delicious
bitter and a bit toasty roasty. toeing a little too hoppy to where i can’t taste the toasty roasty taste but it’s fine. this beer is 8.3 so it could ~knock you down~
such a nice light refreshing ale. would def take on the course (or at home lmao) (gotta work on my swing, gotta do my own thing)
a session ipa that is light but still has those nice bitter hop notes.

i feel like this a drink id have when im chilling on a lounge chair by the pool or at a chill summer bbq, BUT i have the intention of getting a buzz when im doing it. and i mean this as a compliment. this is good good
very tangerine-y and subtly hoppy. despite this being near 7% it’s actually really refreshing. ive eyed this up on the brewery’s insta for awhile so im happy i got it
really really refreshing. flavors classic to a gose with lemon and cucumber bringing you the lightness and refreshingness
only took a small sip of this (thanks uncle jeff). all the flavors that are mentioned to be in it i can taste but the maple is a little strong and somewhat overpowers the other flavors

it’s light and refreshing. the variety of hops in this gives it more of a tropical fruity feel and not a bitter one. some hop varieties i haven’t heard before so an interesting, tropical, fruity flavor

first off, the name and cans are awesome. second, this is a fantastic gose. being this is my favorite type of beer i love to find new ones. haven’t had a non-fruited one in some time so the coriander and salt notes shine with a subtle bready taste
classic traditional hefe with clove and wheat notes.
this is wicked hazy, wicked citrusy, wicked good
very light. it’s got the notes that you’d find in a porter or stout but much much less pronounced and lighter, making this refreshing. Im sure katniss, link, and hawkeye would enjoy this
peach taste is subtle but really refreshing. wheat beer notes come through and balance well with the peach
citrus flavors are pronounced with slight maltiness. This beer has got it going on
has the nice blonde subtly malty notes, with a pleasant blood orange after taste. i swear on an oath to have this every time i come here (if they have it)
a session ipa that definitely doesn’t skimp out on flavor. this is has more power than 18 watts 🤪 sorry

first off, happy 1 year @ seven tribesmen. now for the review. aroma is tart. taste a nice balance of raspberry and peach with a vanilla undertone. finishes tart and kind of dry with some yeast. this beer must be protected at all costs (w/ a shield maybe)

malty and toasty. piney. an amber ale and ipa had a baby. for those that read 20000 leagues under the sea, the ship was called nautilus. as the captain of this ship said, “where others have failed, I will not fail.” this beer does not fail
lemony and tart. slight hint and lavender. finished somewhat try. floral aroma. when life gives you lemons (and lavender) make lavenade
bitter yet refreshing. just like the eye of the storm
tart and refreshing. some floral notes. this has some flower power
the rating of this beer is not uncanny. really aromatic hops give it a citrusy tropical aroma and the taste has those similar vibes with a kiss of bitterness. smooth mouthfeel
nothing crazy. refreshing but nothing crazy
the prickly pear in this very upfront and pleasant. nice and tart. it’s a gose but i don’t taste enough of the salt and coriander. if it had more of that id give it a 4. still very good though
the crushin it brews, well, crush it. citrusy lemony aroma with blueberry tartness with balances the semi bitter hops. also you know im all about a dope beer color
aroma is citrusy. flavor is tropical with notes of bitter pine. my next venture is to name beers after my dogs
light. good balance of lemony hops and malty flavor. this beer is a good hang
i feel like this drink is reminiscent of my journey with alcohol. started with cider, now love ipas. this is sweet yet bitter from the hops.
very crisp. some subtle hop notes. def would enjoy with a crab cake
it’s more bitter than I was hoping for
hoppy yet really refreshing. can is dope too. it’s art and pulpy from the fruity dank hops
really really refreshing and crisp.
v refreshing. as a kolsch should be
guava on the nose is strong, balanced gose with guava notes. I’m a fan
goses are red, violets are blue, i am in love with this drink, and you should be too
lager meets ipa. lagers are my favorite refreshing beer but not totally flavorful so with the hop additions this is nice. i don’t have a pun for this one, a pun WOOD not WORK 🤪
aromatic and piney and citrusy and refreshing. in the world of the cowboys so when in rome
really refreshing. was hoping for a little more hoppy taste but still really good.
really refreshing. like im on an island
a better summer shandy
wheat and hoppy and clean. not really a punch and more of a slap 🤪 it’s refreshing
really dry and a touch sweet.
a session ipa that doesn’t skimp out on flavor. has tropical and citrus noted with a subtle malty taste. def would have all summer break 🤪

have this any season it’s amazing. when a beer lists all the things in it i want to taste them all. and i definitely did. the tart raspberries and blackberries are cut by the vanilla which then finishes by the clean sour taste. mouthfeel is creamy. v good
solid session ipa. light yet really hoppy
they need to serve this up at the krusty krab 🤪 really balanced wheat beer with subtle sweet blueberry flavor
lighter than anticipated. sweet hops balance well with bitterness
this sour is stupid silly good. complex and apple-y and tart. color is dope af though
an interesting twist on a classic beer
sometimes i feel like shandies can get really lemony to the point where it’s too much. this one is a nice kiss of lemon and has a pleasant malt backbone. v good
this is deceptively delicious. not as bitter as you’d think and so smooth. def a sipper though be careful
almost has a wine like taste. this is another good shabang
v good New England. i don’t even have to do a pun for this one — it’s HOPPY and HAZY
this is def funky. feel like the blackberry flavor is muddied. vanilla is present. could be a little more sour
decent sessionable ipa. thought i checked this in before but i guess not. wish the taste was more bitter at beginning and less at end because it finishes more bitter than id expect for a session

hazy. nelson sauvin hops are new to me but i like them. they give beer a winey taste but then the tropical and mango notes found in neipa hops comes through. im not gonna say this beer is the bomb because it’s an obvious pun. thanks Nicolas G. for bringin
refreshing and clean pale ale. i won’t make a good hang joke again
starting early with oktoberfest (actually not, father found a crowler of this in the fridge from a month or so ago). has a roasty toasty taste, malty taste is strong
the malt, subtle bitterness, and light body make this refreshing. but can’t tell if it’s glitter or bubbles im seeing??

beer_name: We Were Made For Peach Other
comment: this was also made for me! peach plays well with the tropical hops. vanilla gives an additional sweetness. really refreshing and smooth
another great good hang. for reference see other reviews for this series
solid hefe. has that yeasty banana notes. the flavors dont ~escape~. little creamier for a hefe but i don’t mind it too much
400th check in on my 25th birthday. this wasn’t my first choice but that’s okay. really piney and traditional, just like me 🤪
i think this is the one I had. herb and coriander flavor is strong in this one but i like it. good wit

comment: first off, you all know im about a good color. second, this REALLY smells and tastes like cotton candy. but it’s not overwhelmingly sweet either.
really light mouthfeel. nelson hops are newish and have a winey taste and i def get them here. a touch bitter but not overwhelming.
never had a grape shandy before. like grape soda but adult version. is a ~touch~ sweet for my liking but if you like a strong grape flavor this is for you
blueberry aroma is strong but taste is well balanced. blueberry flavor is there and subtly malty and bitter. hanging onto whatever’s left of summer!
light and refreshing sour.
good ipa. toes that line between traditionally bitter and piney yet fruity and tropical. o captain may captain
good balance of malt and blueberry taste. aroma of blueberry is strong. also you know im all about a good color
very hazey. hop forward but not bitter — more fruity and tropical tasting. good New England
it’s fall so basic beer drinkers and basic fall bitches like me are having pumpkin beer. this is SWEET but pumpkin flavor is there and wonderful
this is really really good. it almost gives the vibes of a neipa but without being as hoppy and heavy (even though neipas aren’t normally heavy). citrusy, sweet, and light.
pumpkin in this is very balanced with the wheat base. maybe if I drink enough of these I’ll get a pumpkin head 🤪
